==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Satinwood
<hw>Sat"in*wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The hard, lemon-colored, fragrant wood of an East Indian tree
(<spn>Chloroxylon Swietenia</spn>). It takes a lustrous finish, and is
used in cabinetwork. The name is also given to the wood of a species of
prickly ash (<spn>Xanthoxylum Caribaeum</spn>) growing in Florida and
the West Indies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Satiny</ent>⟦br⟧
